# Meta Clash — Go Backend Migration (Final Year Project Grade)

## Problem Summary

Current state: a single-file Node.js backend inside a Next.js API route, with random stats, no auth, no persistence, and flaky external API dependence. This plan migrates to a production-grade Go backend with everything needed for a final year project demo.

---

## Proposed Architecture

```
meta_clash/
├── backend/
│   ├── cmd/server/
│   │   └── main.go                     # Entry point, graceful shutdown
│   ├── internal/
